sources, separately. Our results are in\noverall agreement with those of other distant cluster galaxies. The two target\ngalaxies have molecular gas mass and depletion time that are marginally\ncompatible with, but smaller than those of main sequence field galaxies,\nsuggesting that the molecular gas has not been refueled enough. Higher\nresolution and higher frequency observations will enable us to spatially\nresolve the two sources and possibly distinguish between different gas\nprocessing mechanisms.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Jun 2018 17:32:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 5 Aug 2018 10:26:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-09-26"}
