culations, assuming\ncollinear factorization and introducing $k_T$ broadening, result in significant\nmodifications of the azimuthal distribution at low $p_T$ which must be taken\ninto account in calculations of these distributions in heavy-ion collisions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Jun 2018 19:25:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-09-19"}
